{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi", "name": "Orange-cheeked parrot", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-pyrilia", "name": "Pyrilia", "latinName": "Pyrilia", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Pyrilia（Pyrilia）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联7种鸟类，如Brown-hooded parrot、Rose-faced parrot、Saffron-headed parrot等7种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 7, "x": -94.41, "y": -413.2, "z": 41.27}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi", "name": "Orange-cheeked parrot", "latinName": "Pyrilia barrabandi", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Orange-cheeked parrot（Pyrilia barrabandi）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Orange-cheeked parrot。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -12.91, "y": -705.47, "z": -11.96}, {"id": "bird-orange-cheeked-parrot-d5ce1b8b", "name": "Orange-cheeked parrot", "englishName": "Orange-cheeked parrot", "latinName": "Pyrilia barrabandi", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The orange-cheeked parrot (Pyrilia barrabandi), also known as Barraband's parrot, is a species of parrot in the family Psittacidae. It was formerly placed in the genus Pionopsitta, which is now monotypic. It is found in the Amazonian Andes, in humid lowland forests in the northwestern, southwestern, and south-central Amazon Basin in South America. They are threatened with loss of habitat due to the increasing deforestation of the Amazon. Taxonomy and systematics The binomial name of this bird commemorates the French painter Jacques Barraband. It was formerly placed in the genus Pionopsitta. There are two subspecies: P.b. barrabandi- Found north of the upper Amazon River from east Amazonas, northern Brazil and southern Venezuela to southeast Colombia, eastern Ecuador and northeastern Peru. P.b. aurantiigena- Found south of the upper Amazon River from northern Brazil to eastern Peru and northern Bolivia. Description The parrots are 25 cm (9.8 in) in size and weigh 165–190 g (5.8–6.7 oz). Adults have an olive throat and breast. The thighs are yellow, with the bend of the wing and lesser wing coverts ranging from yellow to orange, and the carpal edge and underwing coverts being orange to red. The tips of the tail and the wing feathers are blue. P.b. aurantiigena has deep orange cheeks, bend of wing, underwing and lesser wing coverts, and thighs, lacking the yellow possessed by barrabandi. They have a black head and orange to yellow cheeks, with a distinctive white eye-ring around a brown eye. The beak is gray to black. Juveniles have a brown crown and olive forehead, nape, cheeks and chin, with a brown margin. The bend of the wings and lesser wing coverts are green with a scattered yellow. The carpal edge and underwing coverts are red with scattered green feathers. Vocalizations Distinctive calls that are reedy and slurred in flight. They have guttural alarm calls. Ecology and behaviour They are active in the early morning. They are often seen singly, in pairs or in small groups of up to 10 individuals at clay banks. Diet They feed on seeds, fruit, and on wasp larvae in galls. Foraging occurs high in canopy or just below the canopy. They also visit clay banks to consume antacid-like soil which neutralizes the acids found in their food. Breeding Their breeding season is possibly from September–October. Distribution and habitat It is found in northwestern Brazil, western Ecuador and Peru, southern Venezuela and Colombia, and extreme northern Bolivia. They are found at elevations of up to 400 m (1,300 ft) in lowland terra firme forest and uncommonly in varzea stands. They also inhabit forest edges and partly disturbed forests. Conservation status The species is listed as least concern on the IUCN Red List. It is susceptible to increasing deforestation in the Amazon rainforest, with its population likely to decrease by 25-30% as it loses habitat. The species is naturally rare in its range. As pets They are uncommonly kept as pets, and are kept as pets in Brazil. References", "shortSummary": "The orange-cheeked parrot (Pyrilia barrabandi), also known as Barraband's parrot, is a species of parrot in the family Psittacidae. It was…", "locations": ["亞馬遜盆地", "南美洲"], "threats": ["森林砍伐"], "lat": -2.3096, "lng": -54.8881, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/ee/Pyrilia_barrabandi_-Napo_Wildlife_Reserve-4.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-pyrilia", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-pyrilia", "species": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi"}, "expandable": true, "x": -12.91, "y": -705.47, "z": -8.15}], "links": [{"key": "bird-orange-cheeked-parrot-d5ce1b8b__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi", "source": "bird-orange-cheeked-parrot-d5ce1b8b", "target": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-pyrilia", "source": "taxonomy-species-pyrilia-barrabandi", "target": "taxonomy-genus-pyrilia", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Orange-cheeked parrot 属于属 Pyrilia。"}]}
